 can be used either under the instruction of a teacher or for self-study. The series was developed over a period of several years and was tested, modified, and expanded after use in the classroom. Language professors and their students or those learning Burmese on their own will appreciate the accessible approach and the manageable size of the lessons of the very practical textbooks in this series.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBurmese languagevConversation and phrase booksxEnglish. 0aBurmese languagexRhetoric. 0aBurmese languagexSpoken BurmesevProblems, exercises, etc. 0aBurmese languagexStudy and teachingxEnglish speakers. 0aBurmese languagexStyle. 0aLiterary style. 4aAsian Studies. 4aLanguage Arts & Linguistics. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh1 aSwe, Daw Khin Mya.1 aTun, U Saw.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978160909222140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781609092221423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781609092221.jpg  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK